                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18210214-13-off87 t18210214-13-crimeloc89"></join>. I called the prisoner to work on the wharf, and about five o'clock I sent him away for the night; between six and seven o'clock I found him in the linen warehouse, I asked what he had about him; he said nothing at all; I said I was certain he had from his appearance, and found three pieces of linen-cloth about his body and in his trowsers. We gave him in charge.</p>
